transcripts.text: There's one right here.  I caught a pretty bad bug when I went back to the UK last week and quite honestly I didn't want to give it to anyone else but then I was reading about Toronto, the UK, everyone's on standby, on high
alert and my friend came with this medical

bag for me to fly with and it included one of these.  so I thought I better be safe than sorry.  Coming through customs, every tenth person was wearing them, obviously all the Chinese people were wearing them.  It was something I've never seen before.
Yeah, you just came in, I think, at the Nexus because three flights have come in from China right now, and you've just come in from where, Heathrow, or did you come in from Gatwick?

Gatwick, yeah, came in from Gatwick on WestJet, but the number of people wearing them at the UK was surprising as well, but anyway, but here, there's everybody, like, a lot of people.  Off and on for a meal, but the ladies, the two ladies next to me, they were both wearing theirs.  And there were a few others on the plane wearing them the whole time during the flight, yeah.
Did you come in from Shanghai or did you come in from... Shanghai, yeah.  Did you?
Were you on business there?  No, no, no, family.
So you're home now?  Yeah, yeah, I'm home now.  And did you wear that the whole flight?
Yes.  And how did you eat?  I didn't eat.  Because of that, no eating.  Most people eat, I didn't.
How long was your flight, the total time?  Did you guys have a stopover or was it a straight flight?
In the airport, did they do any screening, pre-screening to get on the plane?  To check you out, to be okay?
Yeah, the check, I think everyone is okay.
Yeah.  We are safe.  That's when these three flights from China came through.  They're protected with masks.  All of them.  You're coming through at the same time.  What do you think of that?

I think it's fine, but usually they probably check them before they get on board, so that's our hope at least.  But it makes you wonder, right?  Well, you never know exactly.  The virus goes everywhere, so there's not really much about it.
There's a lot of talk about coronavirus down in the States right now, in New York City.  Is there talk about that, or just in general?
People are talking about it.  Actually, I think some people were hesitant to go to the Chinese New Year, but...
We were there and there were a lot of people.
